'''''Carcinogenesis''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[medical journal]] in the field of [[cancer|cancer biology]]. It was established in 1980 and is published monthly by [[Oxford University Press]]. {{As of|2010}}, the [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Curtis C. Harris]] ([[National Cancer Institute]]).<ref>{{citation |publisher=Oxford University Press |title=Editorial Board |url=http://www.oxfordjournals.org/our_journals/carcin/editorial_board.html |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref> ''Carcinogenesis'' publishes articles in four sections: ''cancer biology'' covers the cell and molecular biology of cancer, as well as [[mutation]] and [[DNA repair]]; ''molecular epidemiology'' includes [[Genetics of cancer|genetic predisposition to cancer]]; ''cancer prevention'' covers [[chemoprophylaxis]] as well as dietary factors; and ''carcinogenesis'' covers all forms of [[carcinogen]]s, including their metabolism and detection in the environment.<ref name=About>{{citation |publisher=Oxford University Press |title=About the journal |url=http://www.oxfordjournals.org/our_journals/carcin/about.html |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref> Authors can pay to have their articles released freely online as part of a [[Hybrid open access journal|hybrid open access]] scheme.<ref>{{citation |publisher=Oxford University Press |title=Oxford Open participating titles |url=http://www.oxfordjournals.org/oxfordopen/open_access_titles.html |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref>  Free or reduced-rate online access is available to educational institutions in low-income countries.<ref name=Harris /><ref>{{citation |publisher=Oxford University Press |title=Developing Countries Initiatives |url=http://www.oxfordjournals.org/access_purchase/developing_countries.html |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref>

==History==
The journal was established in 1980 by [[R. Colin Garner]] ([[University of York]]) and [[Anthony Dipple]] ([[National Cancer Institute]]).<ref name=Harris /><ref name=front_1 /> The original scope of ''Carcinogenesis'' was defined in the first issue as research relating to "the prevention of cancer in man", and the journal was conceived from the outset as a [[multidisciplinary]] journal, with the intention of encouraging the "cross-fertilization of ideas" across the "very broad spectrum of scientific endeavour" of cancer research.<ref name=Garner>{{citation |author=Garner C, Dipple A. |title=Editors' Note |journal=Carcinogenesis |year=1980 |volume=1 |issue=1 |url=http://carcin.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/issue_pdf/frontmatter_pdf/1/1.pdf |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref> In 2008, the journal added the subtitle "''Integrative Cancer Research''" to reflect its multidisciplinary scope.<ref>{{citation |author=Harris CC. |title=Editorial |journal=Carcinogenesis |year=2008 |volume=29 |page=1 |url=http://carcin.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/29/1/1 |accessdate=17 August 2010 |doi=10.1093/carcin/bgm257}}</ref>

The journal was originally published by [[IRL Press]],<ref name=front_1>{{citation |author=Anon. |title=Front matter |journal=Carcinogenesis |year=1980 |volume=1 |issue=1 |url=http://carcin.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/issue_pdf/frontmatter_pdf/1/1.pdf |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{citation |author=Anon. |title=Front matter |journal=Carcinogenesis |year=1981 |volume=2 |issue=1 |url=http://carcin.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/issue_pdf/frontmatter_pdf/2/1.pdf |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{citation |author=Anon. |title=Front matter |journal=Carcinogenesis |year=1982 |volume=3 |issue=1 |url=http://carcin.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/issue_pdf/frontmatter_pdf/3/1.pdf |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref> which merged with Oxford University Press in 1989.<ref name=Harris>{{citation |author=Harris CC. |title=Editorial |journal=Carcinogenesis |year=2010 |volume=31 |page=1 |url=http://carcin.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/31/1/1 |accessdate=17 August 2010 |doi=10.1093/carcin/bgp302}}</ref><ref>{{citation |publisher=Oxford University Press |title=A history of journals publishing at Oxford University Press |url=http://www.oxfordjournals.org/news/centenary_history.html |accessdate=17 August 2010}}</ref> 

==Abstracting and indexing==
''Carcinogenesis'' is abstracted and indexed in [[Biological Abstracts]], [[BIOSIS Previews]], [[CAB Direct (database)|CAB Abstracts]], [[Chemical Abstracts Service|Chemical Abstracts]], [[Current Contents]]/Life Sciences, [[Elsevier BIOBASE|BIOBASE]] – Current Awareness in Biological Sciences, [[EMBASE]], [[Excerpta Medica]], [[CAB Direct (database)|Global Health]], [[MEDLINE]], [[ProQuest]], and the [[Science Citation Index]].<ref name=About /> According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2011 [[impact factor]] of 5.702, ranking it 23rd out of 194 journals in the category "Oncology".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2012 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Oncology |title=2011 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |accessdate=2012-12-2 |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>

